Let $F(z)=\frac{z+i}{z-i}$ for all complex numbers $z\not= i,$ and let $z_n=F(z_{n-1})$ for all positive integers $n.$ Given that $z_0=\frac 1{137}+i,$ find $z_{2002}.$
ground_truth:
Iterating $F$ a few times, we get \[\begin{aligned} F(F(z)) &= \frac{\frac{z+i}{z-i}+i}{\frac{z+i}{z-i}-i} = \frac{(z+i)+i(z-i)}{(z+i)-i(z-i)}= \frac{z+i+zi+1}{z+i-zi-1}= \frac{(z+1)(i+1)}{(z-1)(1-i)}\\
&= \frac{(z+1)(i+1)^2}{(z-1) \cdot 2}= \frac{(z+1)(2i)}{(z-1) \cdot 2} = \frac{z+1}{z-1}i,\\
F(F(F(z))) &= \frac{\frac{z+1}{z-1}i+i}{\frac{z+1}{z-1}i-i} = \frac{\frac{z+1}{z-1}+1}{\frac{z+1}{z-1}-1} = \frac{(z+1)+(z-1)}{(z+1)-(z-1)}= z. \end{aligned}\]Thus, $z_{k+3} = z_k$ for all $k.$ Since $2002 \equiv 1 \pmod{3},$ we then have \[z_{2002} = z_1 = \frac{z_0+i}{z_0-i} = \frac{1/137 + 2i}{1/137} = \boxed{1+274i}.\]

We have that
\[F(z) = \frac{z + i}{z - i} = \frac{(z + i)(z + i)}{(z - i)(z + i)} = \frac{z^2 + 2iz - 1}{z^2 + 1}.\]Let $z = x + yi,$ where $x$ and $y$ are real numbers.  Then
\begin{align*}
F(z) &= \frac{(x + yi)^2 + 2i(x + yi) - 1}{(x + yi)^2 + 1} \\
&= \frac{(x^2 - y^2 + 2xyi) + 2xi - 2y - 1}{(x^2 - y^2 + 2xyi) + 1} \\
&= \frac{(x^2 - y^2 - 2y - 1) + (2xy + 2x)i}{(x^2 - y^2 + 1) + 2xyi}.
\end{align*}To simplify this, we want to multiply the numerator and denominator by the conjugate of the denominator:
\begin{align*}
F(z) &= \frac{(x^2 - y^2 - 2y - 1) + (2xy + 2x)i}{(x^2 - y^2 + 1) + 2xyi} \cdot \frac{(x^2 - y^2 + 1) - 2xyi}{(x^2 - y^2 + 1) - 2xyi} \\
&= \frac{(x^2 - y^2 - 2y - 1)(x^2 - y^2 + 1) + 2xy(2xy + 2x) + [(2xy + 2x)(x^2 - y^2 + 1) - (x^2 - y^2 - 2y - 1)(2xy)]i}{(x^2 - y^2 + 1)^2 + (2xy)^2}.
\end{align*}We want to find $z_{2002}.$  Notice that
\[z_1 = F(z_0) = F \left( \frac{1}{137} + i \right) = \frac{\left( \frac{1}{137} \right)^2 - 1 - 2 - 1 + \left( 2 \cdot \frac{1}{137} + 2 \cdot \frac{1}{137} \right) i}{\left( \frac{1}{137} \right)^2 - 1 + 1 + 2 \cdot \frac{1}{137} i} = \frac{-\frac{19049}{18769} + \frac{4}{137} i}{-\frac{18768}{18769} + \frac{2}{137} i} = \frac{-19049 + 1088i}{-18768 + 548i}.\]Then
\begin{align*}
z_2 &= F(z_1) = F \left( \frac{-19049 + 1088i}{-18768 + 548i} \right) \\
&= \frac{\left( \frac{-19049}{-18768} \right)^2 - \left( \frac{1088}{-18768} \right)^2 - 2 \cdot \frac{1088}{-18768} - 1 + \left( 2 \cdot \frac{-19049}{-18768} \cdot \frac{1088}{-18768} + 2 \cdot \frac{-19049}{-18768} \right) i}{\left( \frac{-19049}{-18768} \right)^2 - \left( \frac{1088}{-18768} \right)^2 + 1 + 2 \cdot \frac{-19049}{-18768} \cdot \frac{1088}{-18768} i} \\
&= \frac{\frac{19049^2 - 1088^2}{18768^2} + \frac{2176}{18768} - 1 + \left( \frac{-4133568}{18768^2} - \frac{38098}{18768} \right) i}{\frac{19049^2 - 1088^2}{18768^2} + 1 - \frac{4133568}{18768^2} i} \\
&= \frac{19049^2 - 1088^2 + 2176 \cdot 18768 - 18768^2 + (-4133568 - 38098 \cdot 18768) i}{19049^2 - 1088^2 + 18768^2 - 4133568 i}.
\end{align*}Notice that the real part of $z_2$ is
\[\frac{19049^2 - 1088^2 + 2176 \cdot 18768 - 18768^2}{19049^2 - 1088^2 + 18768^2 - 4133568 i} = \frac{1}{137},\]and the imaginary part of $z_2$ is
\[\frac{-4133568 - 38098 \cdot 18768}{19049^2 - 1088^2 + 18768^2 - 4133568 i} = 1.\]Hence, $z_2 = \frac{1}{137} + i = z_0.$

In general, if $z_n = \frac{1}{137} + i,$ then
\[z_{n + 1} = F(z_n) = F \left( \frac{1}{137} + i \right) = z_0.\]Therefore, the sequence $z_0,$ $z_1,$ $z_2,$ $\dots$ cycles with period 2, so $z_{2002} = z_0 = \boxed{\frac{1}{137} + i}.$
